<div class="bg-brand-lavender bg-opacity-20 rounded-xl p-8 my-8 border border-brand-lavender">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4 flex items-center">
    <svg class="h-6 w-6 mr-2 text-brand-trust" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" />
    </svg>
    Privacy for International Families
  </h2>
  <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-700">
    <p>
      We recognize that health, developmental, and child-related information is deeply sensitive. Whether you are seeking a general consultation or specific behavioral guidance, we are committed to handling your data with care.
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Data Collection:</strong> The platform collects only the information necessary to facilitate your consultation and connect you with the appropriate provider.</li>
      <li><strong>Child Information:</strong> We advise parents to limit the submission of sensitive, identifying minor information via email or contact forms.</li>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Parent or guardian consent is explicitly required before engaging in consultation services regarding a minor.</li>
      <li><strong>EU/UK Privacy (GDPR):</strong> For families in the UK and Europe, you have the right to request access to, or deletion of, your submitted information where appropriate.</li>
      <li><strong>Video Consultation:</strong> Consultations are conducted via secure platforms. Please ensure you are in a private space during your session.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="mt-6 text-sm text-gray-600 bg-white p-4 rounded border border-gray-200">
      <p class="mb-2"><strong>To request data deletion:</strong> Please contact us directly outlining your request, and we will process it in accordance with applicable platform policies.</p>
      <p><em>Emergency Limitation:</em> In cases where there is an explicit threat of harm to self or others, or suspected abuse, providers may have a legal/ethical obligation to break confidentiality to report to appropriate local authorities, though international jurisdiction limits this capability.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
